  <section id="regions" class="section section--snow">
    <div class="section__inner">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">The Archipelago</span>
        <h2 class="section-header__title">Exploring the Banggai Islands</h2>
        <p class="section-header__subtitle">
          The archipelago is split into Banggai Kepulauan (Bangkep) and Banggai
          Laut (Balut). Peleng holds the famous lake and most accommodation;
          Banggai Island is the historical and maritime heart; smaller islands
          offer reefs and isolation for those willing to make the effort.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="region-grid">
        <div class="region-card">
          <div class="region-card__image">
            <Image
              src={mantaRays}
              alt="Peleng Island and Lake Paisupok region"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="region-card__content">
            <span class="region-card__label">Bangkep</span>
            <h3 class="region-card__title">Peleng Island</h3>
            <p class="region-card__desc">
              The massive, mountainous island closest to the mainland. Home to
              Lake Paisupok, the jellyfish lagoon at Paisubatango, and the
              majority of tourist accommodation. The capital is Salakan; Luk
              Panenteng is the village base for the lake.
            </p>
            <div class="region-card__highlights">
              <span class="region-card__highlight">Lake Paisupok</span>
              <span class="region-card__highlight">Jellyfish Lagoon</span>
              <span class="region-card__highlight">Luk Panenteng</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="region-card">
          <div class="region-card__image">
            <Image src={wayagSunset} alt="Banggai Island, Banggai Laut" />
          </div>
          <div class="region-card__content">
            <span class="region-card__label">Balut</span>
            <h3 class="region-card__title">Banggai Island</h3>
            <p class="region-card__desc">
              Further south and east. The historical center of the Banggai
              Kingdom. Feels more maritime, denser, and culturally distinct.
              Banggai Town is built right up to the water's edge, with mosques
              and houses on stilts. Home to the endemic Banggai Cardinalfish and
              the King's Bath.
            </p>
            <div class="region-card__highlights">
              <span class="region-card__highlight">Cardinalfish</span>
              <span class="region-card__highlight">King's Bath</span>
              <span class="region-card__highlight">Island Hopping</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="region-card">
          <div class="region-card__image">
            <Image src={misoolLagoon} alt="Labobo and Bokan islands" />
          </div>
          <div class="region-card__content">
            <span class="region-card__label">Further South</span>
            <h3 class="region-card__title">Labobo & Bokan</h3>
            <p class="region-card__desc">
              Smaller islands offering incredible reefs and isolation. Require
              significant effort to reach-boat charters from Banggai Town or
              Peleng. For those with time and a taste for the remote.
            </p>
            <div class="region-card__highlights">
              <span class="region-card__highlight">Reefs</span>
              <span class="region-card__highlight">Isolation</span>
              <span class="region-card__highlight">Charter</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

