  <section id="seasons" class="section section--white">
    <div class="section__inner">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-header__label">Planning</span>
        <h2 class="section-header__title">When to Visit the Banggai Islands</h2>
        <p class="section-header__subtitle">
          Ideally September to November-seas calmest, rain manageable. Avoid the
          peak of the monsoon (Dec-Feb) unless you have buffer time for delays.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="two-col-text">
        <div>
          <h3>Ideal: September - November</h3>
          <p>
            The seas are calmest and the rain is manageable. This is when the
            Banggai Islands deliver the best experience-reliable ferry
            crossings, clearer water for snorkelling, and fewer cancelled boats.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>January and February:</strong> the winds pick up. The crossing
            between Luwuk and the islands can be cancelled or become dangerous. We
            would avoid the peak of the monsoon unless you have a lot of buffer time
            for delays.
          </p>

          <p>
            <strong>Water clarity:</strong> Paisupok Lake is clear year-round. Heavy
            rains can make the surrounding ocean murky, ruining the snorkelling. Plan
            lake days for any season; ocean days for calmer, drier windows.
          </p>

          <h3>Ramadan</h3>
          <p>
            Travel during Ramadan (dates vary) is tricky. Food stalls close
            during the day. Drivers are fasting and may be fatigued. However,
            the evenings are festive. Plan accordingly if your dates overlap.
          </p>
        </div>

